<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:When compiling for Windows (_WIN32 defined), either branch of the inner Windows-version check uses if (1) { ... } else. For example, with _WIN32 and _WIN32_WINNT >= 0x0600 the compiled code contains: if (1) { tick_start = GetTickCount64(); mono_clock_source = _MHD_CLOCK_GETTICKCOUNT64; } else ... The else (and the code in subsequent alternative branches of the chained if/else sequence) is therefore statically unreachable. This constitutes unreachable code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1.
</scenario>
